Hodgson has been frustrated to see so many players absent from this selection but admits his luck with injuries of late may be coming back to bite him.

'We’ve been a bit unlucky on this occasion, it’s unusual,' he told talkSPORT. 'We’ve been very lucky most of the times we’ve got squads together that we haven’t lost a lot of players.

This time to lose the two goalkeepers (Forster and Ben Foster) for example is an incredible blow. To lose people like (Jack) Wilshere, Lallana, (Alex) Oxlade-Chamberlain, Sturridge, all of whom you think are very important players in the year to come, to lose them all ahead of a qualifier that’s been a bit hard to take.

'But I still think theres enough good ones out there, so I still think we can get 11 good players on the field.'

